Completing our range of services is FastCast – a quick, efficient tool for obtaining immediate weather forecasts for any specified city and state. This feature is particularly user-friendly, offering essential weather information rapidly and succinctly. Orbital Overview is more than just a weather forecasting company; we are at the forefront of technological advancement, with an eye towards a sustainable future for our planet and ambitious plans for space exploration. Our mission is to redefine how humanity interacts with and understands the environment, both here on Earth and beyond, through innovative and freely accessible technology.

Description: Unify Mental Health is a software company which develops systems to operate insurance-funded mental health clinics in the United States.
Full Description: Unify Mental Health is a software company which develops systems to operate insurance-funded mental health clinics in the United States.   Since the start of the pandemic, large companies have began to roll-up all of the small and medium-sized practices in the mental health industry.  This was accelerated by increased demand due to the health crisis, but also the transition from in-person to online care and additional reliance on technology.   This roll-up has put pressure on the existence of small and medium practices, especially those that do not currently accept payment through insurance.  These large companies are afforded the benefits of economies of scale and streamlined relationships with insurance companies.  Without a change in the market, these small and medium-sized businesses will slowly disappear since they cannot compete with these large players. Unify seeks to bring the benefits of a large corporation to small and medium sized mental health practices in the U.S.  This will occur through two principles.  First, through the development of software which can efficiently manage all aspects of a small to medium sized mental health practice.  Current software solutions are not bespoke to the mental health industry, and therefore are not able to operate these practices out of the box.  Second, Unify will manage all aspects of insurance relationships on behalf of the affiliated practices.  This allows Unify to negotiate as a large network on behalf of all affiliated practices instead of a as single smaller entity. Unify has three practices currently working as affiliates, including our in-house brand Meridian Counseling.  We currently have a total of 70 providers with 1150 active patients in both California and Utah.  We are looking for a strategic investor to help us bring this product to market on a national scale.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US

Description: Tappy Technology is a smart city technology that helps cities and its transportation systems become smarter for people with disabilities.
Full Description: Tappy Technology is a smart city technology that helps cities, it's infrastructures, businesses and transportation systems become smarter for people with disabilities. Transportation is defined as the movement of people and goods from Point A to Point B. But, how does an individual with a disability navigate to, or even identify Point A? What happens to them after arriving close to Point B if their mode of transportation does not complete their journey? One of mobility’s toughest challenges for an individual with a disability is providing a safe and simple solution to the First Mile/Last Mile navigation problem. Riders with a disability struggle to travel this short distance to or from a transit stop and points of interest because of physical or other limitations. Tappy Guide mobile application, provides navigation to help locate and identify pick-up and drop-off locations, and building entrances and exits. The user-friendly technology eliminates the First Mile/Last Mile navigation problem such as true, point-to-point, demand-response service.

Description: Simple, Durable and Automatic Equipment Reporting... so humans don't have to.
Full Description: Conceived and built from the ground up by tenured construction owners and contractors determined to create better oversight for their inventory, Rooster will answer the questions, What do I own? Where is it? and When is it being used? The innovative Rooster Asset Tracking System consists of Rooster Hubs and Rooster Activity Trackers. Rooster Hubs are robust data portals that connect to the Cloud using AWS through an LTE-M cellular connection to deliver highly accurate GPS location and activity data. Rooster Activity Trackers are small, rugged devices that, once installed on any piece of equipment, capture activity on a minute-by-minute basis, for up to 5 years, and relay that data to the nearest Rooster Hub. Activity Tracker data transmits through most concrete and metal to any Rooster Hub within and industry-leading ½ mile range using a long-range, low-power pairing design based on the LoRa® communications protocol and protected by more than a dozen patents issued and pending. Proven in the field, Rooster makes finding, monitoring and reporting automatic, delivering real-time visibility into how, where, and when equipment is being used. Easy to order. Simple to setup. All leading to maximized equipment use—and ROI. With more than two decades in the construction industry, the team at Rooster brings you its state-of-the-art toolset to track equipment and report activity so that humans don’t have to. Rooster, Don't Wonder... Know.

Description: Nile is a digital platform that makes it easy for conscientious online shoppers and Black-owned ecommerce brands to connect online.
Full Description: Nile is a digital platform that makes it easy for conscientious online shoppers and Black-owned ecommerce brands to connect online. Users can employ advanced filtering options to search and browse thousands of Black e-commerce brands on our site, and brands can reach their target audiences with greater ease. The problem Nile solves is two-sided. For conscientious consumers, there is a growing demand to support Black-owned businesses in all aspects, particularly when shopping online. Yet, information about Black brands is disjointed and siloed. Plainly speaking, it’s harder to buy Black than it is to buy from Amazon, so where do consumers end up shopping online? Amazon.  For Black ecommerce brands, the problem is even more pressing. Amongst the vast retail noise on the internet, they can’t find their target customers. Our platform aggregates information about Black brands to make it easy for consumers to find them, and to make it easy for brands to market to interested buyers. Without Nile, users spend more time searching for Black brands on search engines or directories that are focused on local businesses and services, and businesses have a harder time reaching a prime (inter)national audience for their products.

Description: PishPosh is the first app to crowdsource community service, like urban trash pickup, and reward those who participate.
Full Description: PishPosh is the first app to crowdsource community service, like urban trash pickup, and reward those who participate. Here's how PishPosh works: users can download the app and log any work they serve in their area. Each minute of work earns them points, which they can redeem to enter giveaways, earn prizes, or, of course, convert to community service hours. The app also features a map that shows opportunity zones, allowing users to easily find areas in need of cleanup. With PishPosh, we aim to expand the scope of community service beyond just trash and clean-up. We envision a future where PishPosh can be used to crowdsource all types of community service, from organizing neighborhood events to volunteering at local charities or even, on a larger scale, supporting disaster relief. We have 2 goals for the next 24 months: reduce recidivism and beautify Californian communities. Jake Curreri founded PishPosh in Paris in October 2022. After spending 4 years at Nike with his first startup, SmallWorld, and gaining global recognition in digital health, he decided to re-focus fitness technology to better the future of our cities. PishPosh is headquartered in San Diego, California.

Description: Developing Open Ocean Farming of Giant Kelp for Renewable Energy
Full Description: Marine BioEnergy is developing a novel system to grow giant kelp in the open ocean. Kelp does not naturally grow in the deep ocean because there are no nutrients in the top layer and kelp needs a substrate for attachment. Marine BioEnergy is building unmanned drone submarines to tow long lines of kelp.  The drones will submerge the farms below the thermocline at night where nutrients are abundant and surface the farms during the day to absorb sunlight. The drones will also submerge the farms to avoid ships and storms. In preliminary testing conducted by a team at the University of Southern California Wrigley Institute, the depth-cycled kelp is growing as well or better than the control kelp. If the kelp continues to thrive in the open ocean environment, the next step is to deploy farms to grow kelp as a biomass feedstock. The proof-of-concept experiments are funded by an award from the U.S. Dept of Energy, Advanced Research Projects Agency - Energy (ARPA-E). We are pleased to be part of the MARINER Program that ARPA-E has funded to launch ocean farming in the United States. (MARINER:  Macroalgae Research Inspiring Novel Energy Resources)
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US

Description: InsurTech dedicated to the transformation of the art and science of reducing property  crime and reduction of insurance fraud events
Full Description: FinRock is transforming the art and science of preventing property crime and the reduction of insurance fraud events. This is done through an identification type agnostic platform which allows users to create personal inventories of their possessions and link them to any current insurance policies. The system provides benefit to the users through identifying property that has been stolen, facilitating its return, and by ensuring that adequate insurance coverage is offered that reflects the user’s actual needs. The platform, through the associated mobile apps, can provide law enforcement, insurance provides and even secondhand dealers with near real time information on the status of an item. If it is found to be stolen or lost, then it can be returned to the owner who is notified of its location. In the case of hotels, universities or hospitals, a lost item can be found as the item just need be scanned to notify its owner that it has been found. Unlike traditional property marking that concentrates on an owner number, the Retrieveit platform allows for the transferring of ownership of an item between users which also adds to the active user base.  Unlike traditional insurance marketing, retrievit starts with the things people own. This approach provides a finer understanding of user needs and allows the targeting of new policies to fill gaps in user policy profile. It is set to position the organization within developing markets such as South East Asia in advance of user insurance demand.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
